  (uuid "78a42c86-1725-59ce-a210-b5a347f36604")
  (paper "A4")
  (title_block
    (title "Flipping Cool Rev A - System Overview")
    (date "2026-05-08")
    (rev "A")
    (company "battle_bots_ai")
  )
  (lib_symbols

  )
  (text "Flipping Cool Rev A schematic-only power/interconnect PCB"
    (at 15.00 18.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.80 1.80)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "98dab426-513d-59ea-815e-80de74ba4184")
  )
  (text "Architecture: 2S LiHV XT30 battery -> manual removable link -> VBAT_SW -> WEKA drive ESC and Pololu D36V50F6 6V BEC. ELRS PWM receiver drives WEKA and two Savox weapon servos. No custom ESC, no required MCU. Optional growth hooks add pit/debug, 3.3V sensor/MCU power, I2C, ADC rail sense, and RGB status LED support."
    (at 15.00 26.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "91f456d7-633f-5e46-b67c-230e8660950c")
  )
  (text "Rail names: VBAT_RAW = battery side of disconnect; VBAT_SW = robot-live switched battery rail; SERVO_6V = external 6V BEC output; RX_6V = filtered receiver branch; AUX_3V3 = optional future logic/sensor rail; GND_PWR = common return."
    (at 15.00 38.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "b119da12-fe53-5afd-abcd-1850b0a4284a")
  )
  (text "Load budget: drive motors 4 x 1.5A stall at 6V = 6A nominal stall reference; weapon servos 2 x 1.4A stall at 6V = 2.8A; BEC target >=4A real headroom, implemented as 6V 5.5A module. 2S directly overvolts 6V motors, so stall duration must be mechanically and operationally limited."
    (at 15.00 52.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "0c2b6c44-91ab-50f2-a178-ca32f5bd105d")
  )
  (text "Validated remote sources: Pololu 3064 motor specs https://www.pololu.com/product/3064/specs ; Savox SH-0255MG+ specs https://www.teamsavox.com/product/sh-0255mgp/ ; GNB4502S80AHV https://www.gaoneng.shop/products/gaoneng-gnb-lihv-2s-7-6v-450mah-80c-xt30-lipo-battery ; SPARC v1.6 https://www.sparc.tools/SPARC_Robot_Construction_Specifications_v1.6.pdf ; Matek ELRS-R24-P6 https://www.mateksys.com/?portfolio=elrs-r24-p6 ; WEKA ESC https://justcuzrobotics.com/products/weka-dual-20-esc-for-brushed-drive ; Pololu D36V50F6 https://www.pololu.com/product/4092 ; Pololu D24V5F3 https://www.pololu.com/product/2842 ; STEMMA QT pin order https://learn.adafruit.com/introducing-adafruit-stemma-qt/technical-specs"
    (at 15.00 73.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.05 1.05)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "ac45a776-0bfd-59ba-8175-8d2d23b6c3f4")
  )
  (text "Safety requirements captured here: mechanical main battery disconnect, visible power indication tied to VBAT_SW, protected battery terminals, and receiver/servo rail isolated from the WEKA logic-only BEC."
    (at 15.00 108.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "ee831889-fe2e-5a36-bb40-194c701f5639")
  )
  (text "Growth constraints: optional MCU/PWM points are passive taps in Rev A; they must not drive receiver-owned PWM nets unless the harness is intentionally reworked. AUX_3V3 is switched off by the main link through VBAT_SW."
    (at 15.00 120.00 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "e51f1d0d-8a69-5387-ae51-557df93f4b50")
  )
  (sheet_instances
    (path "/c7076af1-9a31-5690-879f-805d8afe37e9/" (page "2"))
  )
)
